==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Interested
<hw>In"ter*est*ed</hw> <pr>(⟦icr⟧n"t⟦etil⟧r*⟦ecr⟧st*⟦ecr⟧d)</pr>,
<pos>a.</pos> <ety>[See <er>Interest</er>, <pos>v. t.</pos>]</ety>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>1.</sn> <def>Having the attention engaged; having emotion or
passion excited; <as>as, an <ex>interested</ex> listener</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Having an interest; concerned in a cause or in
consequences; liable to be affected or prejudiced; <as>as, an
<ex>interested</ex> witness; an <ex>interested</ex>
party</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Interestedness</ent>⟦br⟧
